This is a detailed technical site plan showing rainwater management principles for a rooftop garden (taghave). Let me break down the key elements:

DOCUMENT INFORMATION:
- Title: "10. UBEBYGGEDE AREALER"
- Subtitle: "10.3 Principper for regnvandshåndtering"
- Drawing Number: BEA_K00_C08_Dispositionsforslag A3 mappe_5.7.2024

MAIN TEXT CONTENT:
The document explains that the rooftop garden is designed with:
- Plant areas built with a constructed growth medium minimum 350mm thick (DGNB requirement)
- Underlying water reservoir
- System capable of handling normal rain up to T10 events before saturation
- All rainwater on the roof garden flows to planted areas
- Rainwater from higher-lying roofs is collected and connected to the garden's irrigation system

TECHNICAL DRAWING DETAILS:
1. Site Plan Layout:
- Shows a detailed rooftop garden layout
- Includes planted areas represented in green
- Water management features shown in blue
- Building outlines and adjacent structures
- Circulation paths and hardscape elements

2. Technical Annotations:
- Blue arrows indicating water flow directions
- Multiple circular tree/planting symbols
- Detailed notes regarding water management systems
- Reference points for drainage connections

3. Spatial Organization:
- Linear arrangement of planted areas along building edge
- Integration of water management features throughout the garden
- Clear delineation of different surface treatments
- Relationship to surrounding buildings and structures

4. Construction Elements:
- Detailed planting zones
- Water retention areas
- Drainage systems
- Building interface points

The drawing presents a comprehensive technical solution for sustainable rainwater management integrated into a rooftop garden design, with careful attention to water flow, storage, and utilization for plant irrigation.
enrichment_metadata.page_text_context:
First headline here
Tema: 10. UBEBYGGEDE AREALER Emne: 10.3 Principper for regnvandshåndtering
Principper for regnvandshåndtering på taghave
Taghaven indrettet med plantearealer opbygget med et kon- strueret vækstmedie på minimum 350mm (DGNB-krav) og un- derliggende reservoir. Ifølge producenten vil plantearealerne optage normalregn og frem til en T10 hændelse før mætning.
Alt regnvand på taghave tilstrømmer plantearealerne. Regn- vand fra højere liggende paptag opsamles og tilkobles vand- ingssystem i taghaven.
